\theta
0^o < \theta <360^o
\theta \in \left \{ \frac \pi 6, \frac {5 \pi}6\right \}
\theta \in \left \{ 30^\circ, 150^\circ\right \}
 2\sin^2 \theta + 3 \sin \theta - 2 = 0 \\ \sin \theta = \frac {-3 \pm \sqrt{9+16}}{4} = \frac {-3 \pm 5}{4} = \left [ \begin{array}{l} -2 \text{ (spurious solution)}\\ \frac 12 \text{ (correct solution)} \end{array}\right . 
